The paper discusses the incorporation of AI, machine learning, and big data analytics in networking, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also highlights the potential ethical, privacy, and security challenges that may arise with self-driving networks, which could fall under the categories of security and privacy (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of systems thinking tools for analyzing complex social systems is also discussed, which could fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
